title: Treat warnings as errors in pipeline
body:
Configure CI/CD pipeline to treat warnings as errors.  There are 2 reasons for this:

1. We can keep local development settings, within .csproj, to treat style issues as warnings.  This can be discussed, but in my experience this is necessary to keep optimal development flow.
2. The pipeline rejects code that fails style checks.  If the developer forgets to fix style issues before submitting the PR, he/she can at that point correct the style problems, or insert overrides if necessary for the given situation (subject to code review of course).

title: 22 build unit tests
body:
Added unit tests for business entities, use cases, and controllers.  Also renamed the business test cases (from SME as part of user story).

I noticed the way these tests were written introduced some duplication of coverage.  This duplication happens because we have unit tests for everything and because UIQuarter is used by BasePeriod, which is in turn used by CalculateBasePeriod (use case) which is used by BasePeriodController.  So the result seems to be that UIQuarter is really covered 4 times, BasePeriod 3 times, CalculateBasePeriod 2 times, and BasePeriodController just the once.  I'm not necessarily saying this is a problem, but something for us to discuss going forward to make sure DWD is happy with the amount of unit testing coverage - not too little and not too much.

title: #73 GetBenefitYear fails due to invariant culture
body:
Do to a lack of understanding of the dotnet environment variables, the container set DOTNET_SYSTEM_GLOBALIZATION_INVARIANT=1 and it should not have. This was not picked up in unit tests as tests are not run with these environment variables set.

I was able to make the unit tests fail be introducing the environment variables.
https://github.com/flexion/dwd-ui-monetary-lab/runs/4509997114?check_suite_focus=true

I was then able to fix the unit tests here.

title: fixes #95 refactor wage api to accept a quarter list
body:
Fixes #98

Following our discussion of LinqKit this morning I found an alternate implementation that appears to be an improvement on LinqKit and adapted it as a new local shared package, DWD.UI.PredicateBuilder.

Following is the query generated for the Linq to Entities query for the in-memory database, where the ultimate SQL is not available. This is an intermediate syntax based on two year-quarter tuples in the query. As you can see, with an arbitrarily large collection of query tuples, this would quickly become unwieldy, but moreover, I don't know of a way to add OR predicates ANDed to another predicate in Linq.

DbSet<ClaimantWage>()
    .Where(p => p.ClaimantId == <>c__DisplayClass8_0.claimantId && False || (int?)p.WageQuarter == (int?)(int)<>c__DisplayClass8_1.quarter.QuarterNumber && (int?)p.WageYear == (int?)(int)<>c__DisplayClass8_1.quarter.Year || (int?)p.WageQuarter == (int?)(int)<>c__DisplayClass8_1.quarter.QuarterNumber && (int?)p.WageYear == (int?)(int)<>c__DisplayClass8_1.quarter.Year)

title: Spike - Securely calling an on-prem API from GCP
Spike - Google Data Loss Prevention (DLP) Masking
body:
## Summary

Google Data Loss Prevention is a suite of features that help prevent exposure of PII.  Included in the features is a set of APIs for scrambling/masking data.  The team should do a spike on this and determine if the features in the DLP API would suit our needs for masking.  Of particular interest might be the FfxFpe algorithm which retains the format of the original data column and is reversible.  

https://cloud.google.com/dlp/docs/deidentify-sensitive-data#dlp-deidentify-fpe-csharp

Other algorithms and approaches should also be investigated.

### Proposal

Test 1 - Bucket
1. Put some dummy data resembling our claimant table in a CSV in a storage bucket
2. Run the dummy data through the DLP algorithms to de-identify the data into another CSV
3. Run the de-identified data through a reversal process to re-identify the data in a third CSV

The process to run the DLP algorithm might take multiple forms:
1.  Data flow :  https://cloud.google.com/architecture/running-automated-dataflow-pipeline-de-identify-pii-dataset
2. c# code:  https://cloud.google.com/dlp/docs/deidentify-sensitive-data#dlp-deidentify-fpe-csharp
3. [identify others here]


### Tasks

- [ ] Test data is run through DLP and reviewed by DWD BITS DBAs and UI Mod DBAs
- [ ] De-identified data still passes any required integrity checks if stored in existing DB
- [ ] A recommendation on next steps is given and documented in Teams
- [ ] A recommendation on whether to use DLP for our early work is documented in teams
- [ ] Test data is reversed to re-identify and the data is compared to original
- [ ] Spike: load CSV from GCS into Cloud SQL (Postgresql)
